---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy â€¢ Savant"
  description="How I handle your data, in plain language."
>
  <div
    class="mb-12 py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-slate-800 to-gray-900 text-white relative overflow-hidden"
  >
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/20 to-transparent">
    </div>
    <div
      class="w-[90%] sm:w-[80%] md:w-[75%] lg:w-[60%] mx-auto relative text-center"
    >
      <h1
        class="text-5xl max-[371px]:text-3xl font-black leading-tight tracking-tight"
      >
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl mt-4 text-slate-200">
        How I handle your data, in plain language.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div
    class="py-16 w-[90%] sm:w-[80%] md:w-[75%] lg:w-[60%] xl:w-[50%] mx-auto"
  >
    <div class="text-slate-800">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">TL;DR</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4">
        I don't collect any personal data unless you explicitly give it to me.
        No hidden trackers, no creepy stuff. I'm just here to share knowledge.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">What I Collect</h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4">
        By default, I don't ask for your name, email, or any identifying info.
        But if you choose to contribute or interact via GitHub, your public
        GitHub username will naturally be part of that interaction.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4">
        I use <a href="https://posthog.com/" class="text-link">PostHog</a> to collect
        basic analytics - like which pages people visit or what they click. This
        helps me make Savant better, but it's all anonymized. Your identity stays
        yours.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">No Ads, No Trackers</h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4">
        There are no third-party ads, no Google Analytics, no fingerprinting, no
        cookies following you around the internet.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">
        Open Source & Transparent
      </h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4">
        Everything - from this site's code to the content - is open source and
        on <a href="https://github.com/a2ys/blog" class="text-link">GitHub</a>.
        If you're ever unsure about something, you can audit the source for
        yourself.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">Your Rights</h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4">
        Because I don't collect personal data, there's nothing to delete or
        opt-out from. But if you really don't want even anonymous analytics to
        load, feel free to use a tracker blocker (like uBlock Origin or Privacy
        Badger) - no issues with that!
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">Questions?</h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4">
        I'm just a DM or issue away. Hit me up at
        <a href="https://github.com/a2ys" class="text-link">GitHub</a> if you've
        got any questions or concerns.
      </p>

      <div
        class="flex w-full items-center justify-center text-sm text-center md:text-base mt-12"
      >
        <a
          href="https://github.com/a2ys/blog"
          class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-slate-800 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-slate-700 transition-colors duration-200 font-medium"
        >
          View The Source Code on GitHub
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  .text-link {
    @apply border-b border-dotted border-b-blue-600 text-blue-600;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .text-link:hover {
    @apply border-b-blue-800 text-blue-800;
  }
</style>
